<br>
Just dreamin...Verant would never do it..but then who knows what shit they have for us in the &quot;improvements&quot;..heh <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub23.ezboard.com/utargonis.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Targonis</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Forum Wizard</span><br>  Posts: 122<br> <font color=#ffffff>(5/31/01 1:45 pm)</font><br>     <br>ezSupporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Counter spell =&gt; spell reflection?</span><hr size=1> The problem is in balance for the class.  You KNOW they wouldn't give us a buff to do this, and if they did, it would go to every casting class.  Also, because of the nature of buffs in the game, each &quot;use&quot; of the buff to reflect damage back wouldn't take mana from the wizard.  Having it as a skill makes more sense since it would be something that would improve with levels, but also with your mana pool.  You would see that those who are more offensive based would end up out of mana because of this, not because of fizzles or resists, but because the spells were countered.<br>
<br>
Buffs are cute, but until it's a skill, it wouldn't really be an effective tool for wizard duels.  Your mana pool SHOULD be the limiting factor in how long this works, not a random duration, or a fixed duration.<br>
<br>
 <p>Targonis Manastorm<br>
