<br>
I envision Stasis being as such:<br>
<br>
Were I a wizard, I'd cast the spell.  All movement would cease as if under affect of an AoE mez spell.  Duration would be no more than 20 seconds, probably less.  But this would allow everyone to target those in need.  Enchanter targets Ilis for mez (or redies AoE stun), cleric targets enchanter for Remedy, tanks assist on current target, etc.  No looking into spell books, *maybe* hp/mana regen takes place (low duration makes this reasonable), long recast time, and no aggro to wizard for the spell.  Lastly, it could not work on certain mobs (probably those already flagged as unmezzable).<br>
<br>
This would have to be tested to death, but in theory it's functional.  Include the translocate mob (which I view as sending the mob back in time to pre-pull status), and wizards have an entirely new, and proper, dimension with which to work:  Time.<br>
<br>
Caracatan Stormforge<br>
